race.comment: HENLEY EXTREME (5) registered her first win last start over 1420m at this track, getting home by 1.5L. Just missed heavily bet first-up prior, and she's showing plenty of promise. Rides the speed and fitter again looks capable of taking the next step. THIN RED LINE (6) led here from a wide gate beaten a whisker over a mile. Dropping back to 1400m shouldn't bother, and he draws the inside gate this evening. CORSA VELOCE (4) resumes for the in-form Trinder stable and has won fresh. Will race over further and has sprinted well in her last two trials and Byrne Burke sticks from those. She's flying and will give the mare every chance from an inside barrier. GEEGEES LEGACY (7) has needed the two runs this preparation and is proven third-up. His best would have him in the finish and Darmanin sticks aboard is a positive.
